    <subfield code="a">*Brief entry*</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The effects of the Coulomb and c.m. corrections on the Hartree-Fock calculations are explicitly evaluated for several nuclei in the 2s-1d shell. It is seen that the c.m. correction is quite significant for the energies of the lower single-particle Hartree-Fock orbitals and the overall correction to the binding energy can be expressed in the form ( a / A )exp (- bA ), where A is the mass number and a , b are constants. The Coulomb correction is found to increase the gap between the last occupied and the first unoccupied proton orbits and the main correction to the binding energy is proportional to Z(Zâˆ’1)/A 1 3 where Z is the number of protons. The effect of the correction terms on the r.m.s. radii and the intrinsic quadrupole moment of the deformed nuclei is found to be significant (&lt;2%). The effect of these corrections on the mass and charge density distributions is also studied. The calculated r.m.s. radii for both mass and charge distributions in the 2s-1d shell nuclei indicate that the A 1 3 dependence is not valid.</subfield>
